.TH "SYMAIRA" "1" "Apr 2026" "Symaira Vault" "OpenPass Manual"

.SH NAME
symaira-unlock - Unlock the vault and cache the passphrase


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBsymaira unlock [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Unlock the vault by validating the passphrase and caching it in the
OS keyring. This allows MCP servers to start without interactive prompts.

.PP
Use --check to verify if an active session exists without prompting.

.PP
Environment variable OPENPASS_PASSPHRASE can be used in CI/CD environments
but should NOT be used on shared machines (visible in process listings).


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--check\fP[=false]
	Check if session is active (exit 0 = active, exit 1 = expired)

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for unlock

.PP
\fB--ttl\fP=15m0s
	Session duration (overrides config sessionTimeout)


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--profile\fP=""
	use a named vault profile

.PP
\fB--quiet\fP[=false]
	suppress non-error output

.PP
\fB--vault\fP="~/.openpass"
	path to the password vault


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBopenpass(1)\fP
